<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id148d0485-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s625"><num value="625">§ 625.</num><heading> Inapplicability of certain requirements to catfish</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, the requirements of sections 603, 604, 605, 610(b), and 623 of this title shall not apply to any fish described in <ref href="/us/usc/t21/s601/w/2">section 601(w)(2) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id148d0486-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1907-03-04/ch2907">Mar. 4, 1907, ch. 2907</ref>, title I, § 25, as added <ref href="/us/pl/110/234/tXI/s11016/b/1/C">Pub. L. 110–234, title XI, § 11016(b)(1)(C)</ref>, <date date="2008-05-22">May 22, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/1369">122 Stat. 1369</ref>, and <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4/a">Pub. L. 110–246, § 4(a)</ref>, title XI, § 11016(b)(1)(C), <date date="2008-06-18">June 18, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/1664">122 Stat. 1664</ref>, 2131; amended <ref href="/us/pl/113/79/tXII/s12106/a/3">Pub. L. 113–79, title XII, § 12106(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="2014-02-07">Feb. 7, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/981">128 Stat. 981</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id148d0487-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id148d0488-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id148d0489-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> and <ref href="/us/pl/110/246">Pub. L. 110–246</ref> enacted identical sections. <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> was repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4/a">section 4(a) of Pub. L. 110–246</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id148d048a-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/79">Pub. L. 113–79</ref> substituted “not apply to any fish described in <ref href="/us/usc/t21/s601/w/2">section 601(w)(2) of this title</ref>.” for “not apply to catfish.”</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id148d048b-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="id148d048c-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 2014 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/113/79">Pub. L. 113–79</ref> effective as if enacted as part of <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s11016/b">section 11016(b) of Pub. L. 110–246</ref>, see <ref href="/us/pl/113/79/s12106/c">section 12106(c) of Pub. L. 113–79</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t21/s601">section 601 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id148d048d-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Enactment of this section and repeal of <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref> by <ref href="/us/pl/110/246">Pub. L. 110–246</ref> effective <date date="2008-05-22">May 22, 2008</date>, the date of enactment of <ref href="/us/pl/110/234">Pub. L. 110–234</ref>, except as otherwise provided, see <ref href="/us/pl/110/246/s4">section 4 of Pub. L. 110–246</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s8701">section 8701 of Title 7</ref>, Agriculture.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
